reply_body:
Hi OpenOcean team,

Thank you for coming back to me and for the clear steer.

I will submit Aureon through the OpenOcean pitch route with a deck and the key data points you need. I have also checked your current contact page, which points pitch submissions to info@openocean.vc, so I will use that route unless there is a preferred upload link you would rather I use.

For context before the formal submission: Aureon Evidence OS sits in the part of the market where OpenOcean's AI/data infrastructure and automation software themes overlap. It is a local-first AI workflow layer for evidence-heavy business operations: every claim needs a source, every review needs a gate, and every external handoff needs an audit trail.

The first wedge is deliberately practical. SMEs and advisory teams already have the material they need across email, folders, portals, screenshots, documents and code, but they lose time and confidence turning it into controlled grant packs, compliance files, accounting support records and investor diligence material. Aureon turns that scattered work into source-grounded evidence packs with human review, blocked-claim handling and operator receipts.

The reason I think this is more than a workflow tool is the data layer underneath it. As the system runs, it creates structured evidence metadata around what was used, what was excluded, what was reviewed, what changed and what was safe to send. That is the defensible layer: not another generic AI wrapper, but an evidence-control system for businesses that need to move faster without losing proof.

I will keep the submission concise and include:

- product and wedge;
- market and buyer pain;
- current working operator evidence;
- data/workflow moat;
- commercial route;
- stage, roadmap and funding ask.

Best regards,
Gary Leckey
R&A Consulting and Brokerage Services Ltd
